race.comment: Lots of promising types. DANCE ON SON (4) was well fancied on debut and gave a sight but found one better. Surely better for it and won't be as much pressure over the longer journey. Will take beating again. THINK PINK DAZE (9) is a huge chance on the eye-catching debut run back in August. Went back to the tail but came with a barnstorming run to score. Given time and Pike stays aboard. Looks tough to stop again. TRUE FICTION (3) placed over 1400m last time after winning the maiden the start prior over 1000m. Comes back a furlong but has the figures to go close. FRIAR'S LEGACY (1) has been in great form with a win and two minors from three runs this time in. Ran on to just miss in the latest and can find winning form again with the right run. SPIRITED STRIKE (2) drifted back but stormed home to score the maiden last time. This is tougher but on the up and can measure up again.
